#!/usr/bin/perl

=begin metadata

Name: rain
Description: let it rain
Author: Abigail, perlpowertools@abigail.be
License: perl

=end metadata

=cut


use strict;

my ($VERSION) = '1.2';

if (@ARGV) {
    require File::Basename;
    $0 = File::Basename::basename ($0);
    print "$0 (Perl bin utils) $VERSION\n";
    exit;
}

print "/" x 72, "\n" while 1;

__END__

=pod

=head1 NAME

rain - Let it rain

=head1 SYNOPSIS

rain

=head1 DESCRIPTION

I<rain> simulates rain.

=head2 OPTIONS

I<rain> does not accept options.

=head1 ENVIRONMENT

The working of I<rain> is not influenced by any
environment variables.

=head1 BUGS

I<rain> does not have any known bugs.

=head1 AUTHOR

The Perl implementation of I<rain>
was written by Abigail, I<perlpowertools@abigail.be>.

